#: ../../white_version.rst:39
msgid "Assembling the device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:40
msgid "Insert the ESP32 development board onto the breadboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:45
msgid "Mount the lamp stand onto the breadboard, leaving one breadboard slot on both sides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:50
msgid "3. Place the resistor into a free space on the breadboard, and connect it to another free space above or below the lamo stand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:56
msgid "Locate pin **27** on the ESP32 development board. Connect a wire from **pin 27** of the ESP32 to one of the free slot in the same breadboard column as the resistor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:61
msgid "Connect a wire from a **GND pin** of the ESP32 to the other free slot below the LED holder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:66
msgid "7. Connect a wire to each leg of the LED in the lamp bulb. Remember the color of the cables that connects to the short leg LED."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:72
msgid "8. Attach one LED wire to each side of the lamp stand. Ensure that the **long leg of the LED (anode)** is connected to the **resistor side**, and the **short leg (cathode)** goes to **ground**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:75
msgid "Insert the USB cable into the board, and plug it in. The LED should blink."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:77
msgid "Your solar flare alert is now physically assembled and ready to connect to the WiFi."
msgstr ""

#: ../../white_version.rst:79
msgid "Note: the isolation tubes can be settled by warming them. They will reduce their size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:2
msgid "Connecting to the WiFi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:4
msgid "Power on the Solar Flare Alert. After a few seconds, the LED will begin blinking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:6
msgid "If the blinking **stops after a few seconds**, the device has successfully connected to a previously saved WiFi network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:8
msgid "If the LED **continues blinking**, open the WiFi settings on your phone or computer and connect to the access point named **SolarFlareAlert-Setup**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:10
msgid "Once connected, open a web browser and navigate to: ``http://192.168.4.1``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:12
msgid "Select your home WiFi network from the list and enter the password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../wifi_connection.rst:14
msgid "The device will reboot and attempt to join your network. When the LED turns solid green, the connection was successful."
msgstr ""

